### CSS Border Radius

**border-radius** rounds the corners of an element.

---

### Basic Usage

```css
.box {
  border-radius: 10px;  /* All corners same */
}
```

---

### Individual Corners

```css
border-top-left-radius: 10px;
border-top-right-radius: 20px;
border-bottom-right-radius: 10px;
border-bottom-left-radius: 20px;
```

---

### Shorthand (1-4 Values)

```css
/* All four corners */
border-radius: 10px;

/* Top-left & bottom-right | Top-right & bottom-left */
border-radius: 10px 30px;

/* Top-left | Top-right & bottom-left | Bottom-right */
border-radius: 10px 30px 50px;

/* Top-left | Top-right | Bottom-right | Bottom-left */
border-radius: 10px 20px 30px 40px;
```

---

### Circles and Ovals

```css
/* Perfect circle (needs equal width/height) */
.circle {
  width: 100px;
  height: 100px;
  border-radius: 50%;
}

/* Pill shape */
.pill {
  border-radius: 9999px;  /* Large value = pill */
}

/* Elliptical corners */
.ellipse {
  border-radius: 30px / 15px;  /* horizontal / vertical */
}
```

---

### Percentage vs Pixels

| Unit | Behavior |
|------|----------|
| `px` | Fixed radius, independent of size |
| `%` | Based on element dimensions |
| `50%` | Creates circle/ellipse |
| `9999px` | Large value = pill shape |

---

### Common Patterns

```css
/* Circular avatar */
.avatar {
  width: 50px;
  height: 50px;
  border-radius: 50%;
}

/* Rounded card */
.card {
  border-radius: 12px;
  overflow: hidden;
}

/* Button with pill shape */
.btn {
  border-radius: 9999px;
  padding: 10px 24px;
}

/* Squircle (Apple-style) */
.squircle {
  border-radius: 20% / 25%;
}
```

---

> **Note:** `overflow: hidden` is needed with `border-radius` to clip child elements and images.
